The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 Aryan Club will felicitate Sachin Tendulkar on December 22 on the occasion of the clubs 125th anniversary, informed secretary Samar Paul.       
	Sachin will be in Calcutta for the fourth ODI against Sri Lanka and has given his consent to being present at the function. Sachin will be felicitated for completing 20 years in international cricket, Paul said. Sachin turned out for the Aryans in the early 90s in the P. Sen Trophy.          
	 Sayan Sekhar Mondal is likely to make a comeback in the 15-member Bengal squad for the December 8-11 Ranji Trophy match against Uttar Pradesh, in Kanpur.       
	However, it will be Sourav Sarkar who will open the bowling with Ranadeb Bose. The selectors will make a formal announcement on Thursday. With Laxmi Ratan Shukla and Sourav Ganguly there to assist Bose and Sarkar in the pace department, left-arm spinner Iresh Saxena may get a chance in the playing XI.          
	 East Bengals CFL Premier Division match against Calcutta Port Trust, at Salt Lake Stadium, on Sunday, may be rescheduled due to security reasons.       
	Police authorities have informed IFA officials that due to President Pratibha Patils visit on Sunday, they will be unable to provide security at the venue.       
	The IFA is still trying to hold the match on the scheduled date as any delays would see the fixtures going haywire again.          
	 West Bengal Police defeated CLW SA 3-0 in a match of the 114th All India Beighton Cup Hockey Tournament. CCFC beat Behala SA 4-1 in another match.                
